>NAME

if_indextoname - convert network interface index to name

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <net/if.h>
	
	char* if_indextoname(unsigned int 'index', char *'ifbuf');

>DESCRIPTION

This function writes the name of the network interface with index 'index' into 'ifbuf'. 'ifbuf' must be a buffer with at least *IF_NAMESIZE* bytes.

>RETURN VALUE

On success, this function returns 'ifbuf'. On error (the interface with the given index does not exist), it returns *NULL* and sets [errno.6] to *ENXIO*.

>ERRORS

On error, this function returns *NULL* and sets [errno.6] to one of the following:

\* *ENXIO* - 'index' does not correspond to an existing network interface.

